        "## Workflow 7: Zero-Copy Sharing Back to Host\n\n### What Changed\n\nThe isolated pipeline is fully connected (as in workflow 6), but now its outputs **feed back into the host-side pipeline**:\n\n- **ModelSamplingAuraFlow_ZIMG** MODEL → host KSampler\n- **CLIPTextEncode_ZIMG** CONDITIONING → host KSampler (pos + neg)\n- **VAELoader_ZIMG** VAE → host VAEDecode\n\nBoth pipelines produce images from the same models, prompts, and VAE — one running entirely in the child, one running on the host with child-produced inputs.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\nObjects flow **both directions**:\n\n**Child → Host:**\n- MODEL proxy (ModelPatcher)\n- CONDITIONING (zero-copy tensors)\n- VAE proxy\n\n**Host → Child (from workflow 6):**\n- folder_paths, model_management, progress\n\n### Zero-Copy Round Trip\n\nA tensor created in the child’s GPU memory is shared to the host via CUDA IPC. The host uses it directly — no copy, no serialization. This is the full realization of `share_torch=true` with `share_cuda_ipc=true`.\n"
      ],
