      "widgets_values": [
        "## Code: Bidirectional Sharing\n\n### CUDA IPC (`pyisolate/_internal/tensor_serializer.py`)\n\n```python\n# Child serializes CUDA tensor:\nstorage = t.untyped_storage()\nhandle = storage._share_cuda_()\n# Returns: (rebuild_cuda_tensor,\n#   (cls, size, stride, offset,\n#    storage_type, dtype, device_idx,\n#    handle, storage_size, ...)\n# 15 undocumented arguments)\n```\n\nThe CUDA IPC handle is a small opaque byte buffer that lets another process on the same GPU map the same memory. Base64-encoded for JSON transport.\n\n### TensorKeeper\n\n```python\nclass TensorKeeper:\n    def keep(self, t: torch.Tensor):\n        self._keeper.append(\n            (time.time(), t)\n        )\n        # Prevent GC before child\n        # opens the IPC handle\n```\n\nPrevents the host from garbage-collecting a tensor before the child maps it.\n\n### The Full Stack\n\n| Layer | File |\n|:--|:--|\n| Wire format | `rpc_transports.py` |\n| Tensor IPC | `tensor_serializer.py` |\n| Type registry | `serialization_registry.py` |\n| Model proxy | `model_patcher_proxy.py` |\n| CLIP proxy | `clip_proxy.py` |\n| VAE proxy | `vae_proxy.py` |\n| Adapter | `comfy/isolation/adapter.py` |\n| Stub dispatch | `runtime_helpers.py` |\n"
      ],
